commit_message:
Prevent calling waitall() inside a GreenPool's greenthread

When neutron-server is running with several api workers
sending it a termination signal (SIGTERM, SIGHUP or SIGINT)
leads to waitall() being called inside a GreenPool's greenthread.

The reason is that a wsgi server is started in a green thread
from the same green pool that is passed to the server itself
to be used for spawning client green threads.

To avoid it, it is reasonable to use different pools for spawning
a wsgi server and for its internal usage.

This is also the case for metadata agent running with several
metadata workers.

Change-Id: I38174396f06fcb29ac0776534ac6494dabb00df6
Closes-Bug: #1423250

commit_message:
Add Puppet 4.x lint checks

This changes the puppet-lint requirement to 1.1.x, so that we can use
puppet-lint plugins.  Most of these plugins are for 4.x compat, but some
just catch common errors.

This commit also remove custom metadata rake task (this task is now
provided by puppetlabs_spec_helper).

Conflicts:
	Gemfile

Change-Id: Ib87a3874aa09391fff895296162de3c9b1f23334

[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-03-10 16:25:31.000000000', 'files': ['cinder/volume/drivers/dell/dell_storagecenter_fc.py'], 'message': 'Dell FC driver inheritance order causing failures

After commit 610c672998c87e2bf2f919a4fdea86749c748a1f merged
the third party CI test runs for the Dell Storage Center fibre
channel driver started failing. This appeared to be a change
in get_volume_stats calls.

After isolating the cause of this problem it was identified
that the order of the inherited classes for the driver was
resulting in the wrong overridden get_volume_stats call to be
called.

This patch fixes this be just switching the order of the two
parent classes DellCommonDriver and FibreChannelDriver. Swapping
these two results in the correctly overridden call to be made
and CI tests to pass successfully.

Change-Id: I58ec1fde585179037aeca8d449e74d0333fb013d
Closes-Bug: 1430421
'}]
commit_message:
Dell FC driver inheritance order causing failures

After commit 610c672998c87e2bf2f919a4fdea86749c748a1f merged
the third party CI test runs for the Dell Storage Center fibre
channel driver started failing. This appeared to be a change
in get_volume_stats calls.

After isolating the cause of this problem it was identified
that the order of the inherited classes for the driver was
resulting in the wrong overridden get_volume_stats call to be
called.

This patch fixes this be just switching the order of the two
parent classes DellCommonDriver and FibreChannelDriver. Swapping
these two results in the correctly overridden call to be made
and CI tests to pass successfully.

Change-Id: I58ec1fde585179037aeca8d449e74d0333fb013d
Closes-Bug: 1430421

commit_message:
tests: stop generating scenarios for all indexer

We now test only one indexer at a time, as we already rely on tox to
configure correctly one indexer at a time.

This reduces the number of generated+skipped tests and speeds up the
test run.

Change-Id: I974e23a565e43c5156edff18d46a32b768a2294a

rest: return a correct error code if NotImplemented

We currently return a 500 error code if a feature is not implemented in
one of the drivers. It's better to return a nice 501 to the client in
that case.

commit_message:
added check for delay >= timeout in LB add monitor

In network loadbalancer, while adding health monitor
the value of 'delay' should be greater than or equal
to 'timeout' value.

this should be catched before submitting the form
but in the current implementation the form is just
submitted and displaying the generic error 'unable
to add monitor'

this patch is checking this condition and displaying
the specific error without submitting the form.

Change-Id: Iac7cb4871e25ca2dc7e8bbdb1e35a2881a4c6d7a
Closes-Bug: #1430235

commit_message:
Preserve preexisting ports on server delete

When using the '--nic port-id' option for nova boot to bind
a server to an existing port, nova deletes the preexisting
port on server terminate (delete). This behavior is not correct
since the user has preallocated the port object and will
expect it to only be unbound from the server on delete.

This patch allow the existing port to be unbound from the instance
on server delete whereupon the port will still exist but not
be associated with the instance in neutron (note the '--nic
port-id' opt is only supported with neutron). The patch also
adds unit tests to verify the behavior + changes.

This patch also moves instance.info_cache.delete() to be called
after _shutdown in the compute manager as shutdown calls
deallocate_for_instance so the info_cache is still needed at this point.

Based on original work from Aaron Rosen <aaronorosen@gmail.com>
for which you can see a stale patch review here:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/77043/

UpgradeImpact:

Existing applications that created neutron ports and assigned them to a running
instance or to a instance that is created will need to be aware
that they are now respponsible for the deletion of the ports and that these
ports will not be deleted by nova when the instance is destroyed.

Co-authored-by: Aaron Rosen <aaronorosen@gmail.com>
Co-authored-by: Davanum Srinivas <davanum@gmail.com>

Change-Id: Ia5367cf064d40690670ffeac3c1f16998464c234
Closes-bug: 1158684

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-03-07 07:20:39.000000000', 'files': ['horizon/static/horizon/js/horizon.tabs.js'], 'message': 'Narrow selector to eliminate JavaScript keydown perf hit

The users data (/identity/users/) can get quite large in
some environments. In one of our environments, we have 800+
users. The users table on the index page is not paginated,
and so shows all 800+ users.

If you attempt to create a new user using the "Create User"
modal form, keyboard performance dies. It can take several
seconds for each keystroke to register in each input field
on the form.

It turns out that there is are several event handlers bound
to the "keydown" JavaScript event, at the level of the
document itself. This has been done to ensure that dynamic
content gets handled properly. In the case where we have
several hundred rows of data on the page, this is killing
performance.

The solution: bind the event handler to the highest level
element in the document necessary to handle the required
event. The focus of the JavaScript in play here is to
enable keyboard navigation between tabs in a form. Tab
groups will always have a DIV with a class attribute of
"tab-content". So we now bind our event handlers to that
class instead of the overall document.

Closes-Bug: #1411892
Change-Id: I9a37fb20a2506b1dabffc5f2b0b7b97341de5335
'}]
commit_message:
Narrow selector to eliminate JavaScript keydown perf hit

The users data (/identity/users/) can get quite large in
some environments. In one of our environments, we have 800+
users. The users table on the index page is not paginated,
and so shows all 800+ users.

If you attempt to create a new user using the "Create User"
modal form, keyboard performance dies. It can take several
seconds for each keystroke to register in each input field
on the form.

It turns out that there is are several event handlers bound
to the "keydown" JavaScript event, at the level of the
document itself. This has been done to ensure that dynamic
content gets handled properly. In the case where we have
several hundred rows of data on the page, this is killing
performance.

The solution: bind the event handler to the highest level
element in the document necessary to handle the required
event. The focus of the JavaScript in play here is to
enable keyboard navigation between tabs in a form. Tab
groups will always have a DIV with a class attribute of
"tab-content". So we now bind our event handlers to that
class instead of the overall document.

Closes-Bug: #1411892
Change-Id: I9a37fb20a2506b1dabffc5f2b0b7b97341de5335

A previous commit 799e288f48e5d99731dedbfb94808a8cbe01c05c
has broken the ability to recognise long URIs (>8192) and
raise an exception used to prevent the excessive URI being sent
to the server. This impacts the commands net-list and

The previous edit removed one of the duplicate _check_uri_length functions.
This edit 'swaps' the removal and updates the unit test stubbing accordingly.

The capability to split excessive URIs into managable chunks remained in
the code, but no longer executed because this exception was not raised.
It should be noted that as a side effect of recognising the
long URI, data is returned with the exception that indicates
'how excessive' the URI length was. This allows the URI to be
broken into chunks that will be supported.

Restore the capability to recognise that an excessive URI has
been provided and to raise the expected exception with
related data.

Closes-Bug: #1422736
Change-Id: I1b719bed406b83c5f2deac06e127798a91f51ad7

commit_message:
Reinstate Max URI length checking to V2_0 Client

A previous commit 799e288f48e5d99731dedbfb94808a8cbe01c05c
has broken the ability to recognise long URIs (>8192) and
raise an exception used to prevent the excessive URI being sent
to the server. This impacts the commands net-list and
security-group-rule-list.

The previous edit removed one of the duplicate _check_uri_length functions.
This edit 'swaps' the removal and updates the unit test stubbing accordingly.

The capability to split excessive URIs into managable chunks remained in
the code, but no longer executed because this exception was not raised.
It should be noted that as a side effect of recognising the
long URI, data is returned with the exception that indicates
'how excessive' the URI length was. This allows the URI to be
broken into chunks that will be supported.

Restore the capability to recognise that an excessive URI has
been provided and to raise the expected exception with
related data.

Closes-Bug: #1422736
Change-Id: I1b719bed406b83c5f2deac06e127798a91f51ad7

commit_message:
Updated Wizard Help Panel Design

This patch changes the color of the help panel and adds a border
arround the panel and button in order to better separate it from
the underlying wizard forms. Previously the forms and the help panel
shared the same background color. This makes the help panel more
distinct without introducing new colors and retains minimalist design

Mockup: http://invis.io/2W2CNGUBE

Partially Implements: blueprint launch-instance-redesign

Change-Id: I063b359cf7abf9bd9c0f782cda65b01763d4c4fd

commit_message:
Double check admin password when update user password

Add a new setting to enable a new textbox field on the Change
Password form that will double check the logged-in Admin
user's password.

For example if the logged-in admin leaves an unattended computer,
someone can change the password of the logged in user successfully.

Co-Authored-By: Steve Martinelli <stevemar@ca.ibm.com>

Change-Id: Icafa8ce8ab30ec43d3f6419a77118a634a163870
Closes-Bug: #1387372

commit_message:
FIP debug messages

The experimental DVR test job is seeing intermittent failures
related to FIPs.  This patch will add debug log messages to the
l3-agent to help debug the failures.  These logs messages will
indicate when fips have been added and the fip statuses before
they are sent to the plugin.

commit_message:
Stop using [orchestration] image_ref

There are no remaining heat tests which require heat-cfntools on
the test image, so orchestration tests can just use [compute] image_ref
(AKA cirros).

test_neutron_resources has been modified to use curl instead of
cfn-signal.

This will close tempest bugs where fedora boot times out in general
gate jobs.

Change-Id: Ic70c4b5859183b9ebc716dec3095cefc62be5af7
Closes-Bug: #1430524

commit_message:
Check for new versions of get-pip.py

People can leave their devstack installs around for a long time, and
in the mean time new versions of pip can be released.

The current check does not download a new version if an old one
exists.  We want to check for new versions, but we also don't want the
gate jobs trying this sometimes unreliable fetch.

So add a flag-file that tells devstack if it downloaded get-pip.py
originally.  If so, on each run check for a new version using curl's
"-z" flag to request only files modified since the file's timestamp.

Change-Id: I91734528f02deafabf3d18d968c3abd749751199
Closes-Bug: #1429943

commit_message:
Refactor: remove dep on trust_api / v3 token helper

This removes the Fernet token formatter's dependency on both trust_api
and the v3 token data helper, leaving token formatters with nothing to
deal with other than primitive data. The responsibility of managing
token_data objects is left entirely to the core token provider.

Change-Id: I7e7effa769d2c25a3ea6dafa7ab4d34c055193de

commit_message:
Updating alembic HEAD file according to the current code.

The commit I9f67a82b0e0a493ff8b39424296699e7e517e9df added a new
alembic script without updating the HEAD file.
This is harmless since the command :
neutron-db-manage --service vpnaas ... upgrade head
will still apply the alembic script, even if the HEAD file is
not correct.

Change-Id: Icf22c88686edd60f1452afd631897c5d709fdcb7

commit_message:
VPNaaS: Enable StrongSwan in gate hook

To support running the new neutron-vpnaas-dsvm-functional-sswan functional
job, this commit enables StrongSwan process for DevStack, when the argument
passed in is dsvm-functional-sswan. The existing functional job,
neutron-vpnaas-dsvm-functional, uses the argument dsvm-functional, which
will use OpenSwan.

In addition, tox commands are modified so that dsvm-functional will run
the tests in tests/functional/openswan/, and dsvm-functional-sswan will
run tests in tests/functional/strongswan/.

Both jobs will use the load_tests method in __init__.py to also run test
modules in tests/functional/common, in case there are tests that are
common to both jobs.

README files were added to indicate what each directory is used for, and
dummy test modules created to verify the jobs.

Lastly, a coverage command (dsvm-functional-sswan-cover) was created
to provide coverage for StrongSwan specific tests.

Change-Id: I78a053c71fa87eab2d1f1585dd4c261506e34644
Partial-Bug: 1424757

commit_message:
Add the missing parameter agent_mode to the FWaaSDriverBase class methods

The change-Id of Iba78e534ccf347ea6270aabc939a489dd40a7b9e introduced the
"agent_mode" parameter to the methods in the FWaaSDriverBase class. This patch
set adds the "agent_mode" parameter to the create_firewall, delete_firewall,
update_firewall and apply_default_policy abstract methods to maintain
consistency.

Closes-Bug: #1418196
Change-Id: Icb2d2db56b35cd4304bfcf2c2abae2dbc5ea9579

commit_message:
fixed row update for loadbalancer tables

In loadbalancer when creating pool or member
the corresponding row is not updating as per
the status change

manual page reload is needed to see the
current status

this patch added a row update class.
this will update the current row as per
the status change.

Change-Id: I4a3fed098e2e04aec5d72d83618a40e086b0a16c
Closes-Bug: #1425057

commit_message:
Stop installing unittest2 from deb packages

The version installed is conflicting with the version required in
testtools-1.7

While a better solution is to dig through and figure out what is causing
the transitive floating dependency that installs testtools 1.7
this should fix the issue for stable/icehouse. And we need to fix
stable/icehouse to fix stable/juno (because grenade) which in tern is
needed to unbreak master branch.

Change-Id: Ib193e18afbb60c43d8dd66444bbf367689837182
Partial-Bug: #1430592

commit_message:
Better logging of resources

Consolidate a bunch of logging messages into one when syncing resources.
This reduces a lot of log messages for virt drivers that manage a lot
of nodes within the same nova-compute. This also now logs the node name
with the resources, so you can actually tell which node we're talking
about.

Change-Id: I0ee9c9c5913d48b96f70250ed5540424d88c083b

commit_message:
ofagent: Have a thin driver module

It seems preferable to have a thin driver module
rather than directly referencing an external module in setup.cfg.

This also introduces "ofagent" directory which can be used to
put requirements.txt later.

Closes-Bug: #1412653
Related: blueprint core-vendor-decomposition
Change-Id: Id86ade4ae75dceb5ce4283869f42f4c0d1af7c4d

commit_message:
Introduce Guru Meditation Reports into Designate

* Pick GMR implementation codes from oslo-incubator
* Add SIGUSR1 signal handlers in each Designate service
* Add GMR docs

Change-Id: I7c3938dfa5e0100a6b28b9bdf0afcf3c135dd37c
Implements: blueprint guru-meditation-reports

commit_message:
MTU selection spec update bridge_mappings new format

Update the spec with the revision of the agreed
per bridge_mappings/physnet MTU setting format.  This
removes reference to the bridge_mappings config as it
is per-instance of compute-node agent, thus, a scale
and usability problem to use that as a vehicle for
providing this info.  The implementation in review
 https://review.openstack.org/153733/
will need to be revised to match the new proposal.

blueprint mtu-selection-and-advertisement

Change-Id: I7bfe4fc5c58a3894785835f028b3fc7e8dcb2f9c

commit_message:
Check unsupported query filters of listing events

Currently, CLI cannot recognise the unsupported query filters
of listing events, this is unlike others commands (
listing alarm, etc.). This patch provides a clear
presentation for valid keys if we specify unsupported
keys in query fields.

Change-Id: I9b8ef306b97b3102c7a1c8d8d451a7be427e37ae
DocImpact: check unsupported query filters of listing events
Closes-Bug: #1291846

reviewers: [{'_account_id': 3, 'name': 'Jenkins', 'username': 'jenkins'}, {'_account_id': 1955, 'name': 'Alan Pevec', 'email': 'alan.pevec@redhat.com', 'username': 'apevec'}]
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-03-10 11:58:22.000000000', 'files': ['openstack/common/rpc/matchmaker_redis.py', 'tests/unit/rpc/test_matchmaker_redis.py'], 'message': 'Fix matchmaker_redis ack_alive fails with KeyError

Fix matchmaker_redis: ack_alive fails with KeyError on re-registration
attempt.

def ack_alive(self, key, host):
    topic = "%s.%s" % (key, host)
    if not self.redis.expire(topic, CONF.matchmaker_heartbeat_ttl):
        # If we could not update the expiration, the key
        # might have been pruned. Re-register, creating a new
        # key in Redis.
        self.register(self.host_topic[host], host)

self.host_topic is a dict with keys of tuple (key, host), not 'host',
register's first parameter is the topic like 'notification-info',
so modify it to key.
And it will not cause indefinite recursion, because when register end,
the key exist in redis, redis.expire will return True.

Add test case for ack_alive.

(backported from oslo.messaging; omitting master branch since it does
not have RPC module anymore.)

Closes-Bug: #1419718

Change-Id: I8d972afe89aec02a5c8f0d9dd4e216bc12c298a1
'}]
commit_message:
Fix matchmaker_redis ack_alive fails with KeyError

Fix matchmaker_redis: ack_alive fails with KeyError on re-registration
attempt.

def ack_alive(self, key, host):
    topic = "%s.%s" % (key, host)
    if not self.redis.expire(topic, CONF.matchmaker_heartbeat_ttl):
        # If we could not update the expiration, the key
        # might have been pruned. Re-register, creating a new
        # key in Redis.
        self.register(self.host_topic[host], host)

self.host_topic is a dict with keys of tuple (key, host), not 'host',
register's first parameter is the topic like 'notification-info',
so modify it to key.
And it will not cause indefinite recursion, because when register end,
the key exist in redis, redis.expire will return True.

Add test case for ack_alive.

(backported from oslo.messaging; omitting master branch since it does
not have RPC module anymore.)

Closes-Bug: #1419718

Change-Id: I8d972afe89aec02a5c8f0d9dd4e216bc12c298a1

commit_message:
Fix matchmaker_redis ack_alive fails with KeyError

Fix matchmaker_redis: ack_alive fails with KeyError on re-registration
attempt.

def ack_alive(self, key, host):
    topic = "%s.%s" % (key, host)
    if not self.redis.expire(topic, CONF.matchmaker_heartbeat_ttl):
        # If we could not update the expiration, the key
        # might have been pruned. Re-register, creating a new
        # key in Redis.
        self.register(self.host_topic[host], host)

self.host_topic is a dict with keys of tuple (key, host), not 'host',
register's first parameter is the topic like 'notification-info',
so modify it to key.
And it will not cause indefinite recursion, because when register end,
the key exist in redis, redis.expire will return True.

Add test case for ack_alive.

(backported from oslo.messaging; omitting master branch since it does
not have RPC module anymore.)

Closes-Bug: #1419718

Change-Id: I8d972afe89aec02a5c8f0d9dd4e216bc12c298a1

commit_message:
Make resource creation return 400 with empty manifest

When resource pod/rc/service is created with no
manifest, 500 status is returned to user due to
unhandled exception. This patch make this resource
creation return 400 status to user when no manifest
is passed. Also added test for empty manifest.

Change-Id: I7f6edc5bc7f8d46ea0eb0b71e22d2b88b3482154
Closes-bug:#1429767
Closes-bug:#1430064

commit_message:
Add callback to allow controller notification of allocation change

This patch adds a simple callback mechanism to allow the controller
embedding a transfer table to be notified when the allocation in
the table has changed.

This is needed so that panels in the launch instance wizard can
update the launch instance model when the allocation changes.

Change-Id: I2c6fc35aedeeb9e58e2f08fafa293bc45cdd92af
Partially Implements: blueprint launch-instance-redesign

commit_message:
Make sure we don't log the full content of the config drive

The config drive content can be pretty heavy, so let's make sure we
don't log it.

Plus, this commit is changing the log level from INFO to DEBUG, which
is the right one for that message.

Closes-Bug: #1429208
Change-Id: I383886a72b3930b261c02027c8c93779432b3e45

commit_message:
Added tox tempest environment

When running tox with tox -etempest, tox will install tempest
from a specific commit that the v2 tests are known to work well
with.  Then the tests will be run. This also puts a change in
pretty_tox.sh to control the concurrency level because the
tempest tests will fail when running in parallel.

Change-Id: I745293322149390f0e709165f34c144f5c439720

commit_message:
Datestamp the generated test image

Copying to tarballs.openstack.org is not atomic, so the image
name needs to include a datestamp and the publish mechanism needs
to symlink to the lastest image.

Change-Id: I7ffba492812beca39cdb773d9e284750a3a80878

commit_message:
added security group to create cluster call

- Added a configuration item, os_security_group, to api to allow
  a default security group to be specified
- Added tests to test_create_vm to verify invalid security group
  results in a failure
- Modified nova fixture to check for security_groups in vm create
- Modified neutron create port to include security_groups
- Modified devstack plugin to create a security group for rabbitmq

Change-Id: Ib8490b15b0e90812d630d237cc4fcc8d0c8a4f9a

commit_message:
Delete assemblies when plan is deleted

Presently deleting a plan (app) fails if any
assemblies, READY or otherwise, reference that plan.

This patch adds a destroy_app function to deployer
to asynchronously delete a plan's assemblies before
deleting the plan. The existing destroy function
has been renamed to destroy_assembly to reduce
confusion.

Closes-Bug: 1422500

Change-Id: Idc10e317c0502001ef847b38b690cf67e9826022

commit_message:
Mock RPC _send method in BaseTestCase

The purpose of this patch is to get rid of this sort of spam:
http://paste.openstack.org/show/183145/
I don't understand the deal with the fake RPC transport.
It's sending out a message, and waiting for a reply from... Who?
One solution is to just mock the _send method of the fake RPC transport.
Another would be to change the behavior in the Oslo messaging fake driver.

Change-Id: I22227f19c347b3f43cbea214249f29eba4dccc09

I've only seen this happen once, however by making the token expiry 5

commit_message:
Fix time issue in AccessInfo test

I've only seen this happen once, however by making the token expiry 5
minutes in the future, then checking that it wont have expired in 300
seconds means that if the test happens all on the same second boundary
then the test will fail.

Just increase the time we're checking for by a second to ensure it
doesn't happen.

Change-Id: Iadeadfbacaf6f1b939c237919b52445c60c9bdd0

* extra_context in the SetFlavorChoiceAction.get_help_text
    (panel project.instances) ;

    (panel project.volumes).

commit_message:
tests: initialize policy in BaseTestCase

This is needed to avoid test cases breaking policy file search code from
oslo.config by mocking out stdlib functions from os module like
os.path.isdir or os.path.exists.

This also allows us to remove explicit policy setup from test_api_v2 and
test_policy files.

Note that for test_netns_cleanup, test_ovs_cleanup, and test_config, we
removed test_setup_conf test cases. They test a function that is used in
other test cases only, and hence do not belong to the suite. This allows
us to avoid hacks around those test cases that do not play nice with
global config-file options we set in BaseTestCase.

Change-Id: If14a3c741837193ad104467f0cf4486a6a386e6d
Closes-Bug: #1426369

commit_message:
Fix display name change during backup restore

Currently the display name and description of the target volume
is changed to that in the backup meta-data during backup restore.
This can confuse the end-user, especially in the case of restore
to an existing volume. This patch removes display name and display
description from the list of fields to be copied from the backup
meta-data to update the volume.

Change-Id: I21a0505352ddc8db801f4820d575399a4771b259
Closes-Bug: #1376194

commit_message:
VMware: prevent exception with migrate_disk_and_power_off

Commit 8e4a9156f4dccf003970848c28b8a9d15c55212d ensured that
all instance operations that do not require a cluster or
volume will make use of the base _vmops class.

The method migrate_disk_and_power_off was missed.

Change-Id: Ibfdd9407905acc5e9a3e3a97a76fb2e35a68e817

I noticed these telemetry classes were overloading repr.  The
reason they were doing this is they have to resource key or name,

commit_message:
Remove repr calls from telemetry classes

I noticed these telemetry classes were overloading repr.  The
reason they were doing this is they have to resource key or name,
but repr doesn't use that anymore.  We should use the base class
repr.

Change-Id: I3a7090eb42fcc12f15d791172c2b63b3dbc85edf

commit_message:
Add OSWL collector keystone user

Adds keystone user for gathering OpenStack
workload statistics. A separate user is needed
in case the administrator changes the default
user credentials. Further details about OSWL
collector in blueprint.

Change-Id: Idfc669b882c2c32a3805b36ffc58b27c58048e6d
blueprint openstack-workload-statistics
Closes-Bug: #1427270

commit_message:
Fix removal of backup segments

When removing any object, freezer will check the object's metadata
to identify the presence of associated segments

This results in the correct removal of all parts of old backups

Change-Id: I03cedc47a581615b6a214ed9e32e99c0e6f91db9
Closes-Bug: #1429915

commit_message:
Main loop refactor

The code relative to the various actions is moved into their
respective job objects.
A factory function creates the correct type of job object according to
the action requested.
This replaces the long "if" chain in the main loop

The main loop calls the Job object's execute() method.

Change-Id: Iec1acfe62575ba062f9b56171784d1d74dc86556

commit_message:
Cleaned up redundancy between instance update() and edit()

The instance service.py was functionally redundant with respect
to 'configuration' functionality. This change modifed update()
to update its body with appropriate configuration for edit(),
then delegate processing to edit().

No APIs were changed.

Tested using trove configuration-attach/detach and update with
--configuration and --remove-configuration CLIs.  Existing API
tests were deemed sufficient.

Modified the implementation to include a new method,
_modify_instance(), which is called by both update() and
edit().  In the previous implementation, update() called
edit() directly.

Added unit tests for _modify_instance().
Modified _modify_instance() unit tests per Eddie's comment.

This is a partial fix for bug 1364701.

Change-Id: Iaf198922ffbb4c4493309861902b1d16ffe739ec

commit_message:
Remove shelve policy for nova compute layer

There are compute layer policy for shelve related
functions (shelve, unshelve, shelve_offload). However,
API layer already have the policy check and EC2
code do not have shelve policy. So keep the policy in the
compute layer doesn't make sense.

Prtially implements bp v3-api-policy
DocImpact

Change-Id: I2fd74bd58fc11d6afa5512a843e02a709e17124a

There's been a long running issue observed in the
tempest test test_rescued_vm_detach_volume

The symptoms are detach/delete failures on the

seems to be happening is that during rescue of

commit_message:
Give attachments time to stabilize on unrescue

There's been a long running issue observed in the
tempest test test_rescued_vm_detach_volume

The symptoms are detach/delete failures on the
cinder side due to timeouts or just extremely
long running LVM commands.  It turns out what
seems to be happening is that during rescue of
an instance with an attached volume, there's
a bit of swapping of devices on the compute node.

What happens is that during unrescue, we return
the instance back to ACTIVE however the device
paths haven't been updated properly, and as a
result when we try detach/delete of the volume in
our tempest tests LVM hangs waiting for an invalid
device to timeout.

This is mostly a temporary work-around until we
can figure out a better way to do this than a
dumb sleep.  We should be able to figure out
exactly what the state of the connections is
and how to monitor them until we know that
we're officially "done" with the unrescue.

Change-Id: Ib9f6b6569235d0ebd095a35e5f8566836d327793
DocImpact: update nova.conf docs
Closes-Bug: #1423654
Partial-Bug: #1373513

commit_message:
Fix delete a secret that does not exist

Changes the behavior of deleting a secret that does not exist.
The secret uuid is now verified as a valid UUID. If it not a valid
uuid it will result in a value error. A valid uuid will be allowed
to go through to the server and a 404 will be returned if the secret
does not exist.

Change-Id: I35e7fa36714604c2beba044d0e8bb492233bb7a4

commit_message:
Support to move the horizon relative to web root

When deploying Horizon, on a web server, where other applications
are used, it's quite handy to be able to move Horizon around quickly.
This change introduces a single Variable WEBROOT to achieve this.

Implements: blueprint shared-webserver

Change-Id: Ic731f6754e233b328a8dbe7026b1d7417620fd66

commit_message:
Don't notify dead DHCP agent of removed networks

This is needed to avoid a case when agent sees network
removal notifications on startup. Processing of those notifications
may overlap with processing of active networks and DHCP might be
disabled on some of active networks as a result.

Change-Id: I8271e8fce8b4d80a339f598b98467694774a299e

commit_message:
Prevent calling waitall() inside a GreenPool's greenthread

Keystone eventlet wsgi server is started in a green thread from
the same green pool that is passed to the server itself
to be used for spawning client green threads.

To avoid it, it is reasonable to use different pools for spawning
a wsgi server and for its internal usage.

Change-Id: I1246e2b730a522480ed495fbb53ae376ee7593d5
Closes-Bug: #1423250

Commit 0f65a294d90d69fe6ad2047dc5f63ad362787926 fixed the

commit_message:
libvirt: fix tracing and unicode handling in firewall._get_filter_uuid

Commit 0f65a294d90d69fe6ad2047dc5f63ad362787926 fixed the
UnicodeEncodeError possibility in the debug message if the exception has
unicode in it, but introduced the usage of exc_info=True which is
dumping nearly 800K traces in normal gate runs since 3/3.

The better way to fix this bug is to keep the message the way it was
before the change that uses exc_info=True but cast the debug log message
argument as unicode.

An alternative is casting the exception variable with six.text_type, but
according to the oslo.i18n team the guideline is to make debug log
messages unicode if you're substituting in exception variables.

Adds a unit test to exhibit the bug and verify the change.

Closes-Bug: #1430383

Change-Id: I66d28c280ec6bc637d7363291ebc69fda9ca66d9

commit_message:
Increase flexibility with managing client keys in profile

This commit introduces the client_keys hash parameter to
ceph::profile. This allows one to use the profile to inject
and configure any client keys with any parameter.

Backwards compatibility is *NOT* maintained for the purpose
of staying as clean and as simple as possible in the context
of drafting the first stable release of puppet-ceph.
This avoids shipping the first stable release with, already,
a deprecation that will have to be maintained throughout an
entire release cycle.

Some tests have been added and test coverage is in general
improved as part of this commit.

Change-Id: Ie6adbd601388ab52c37037004bd0ceef9fc41942

commit_message:
Additional test coverage for password changes

Keystone has four API calls which may result in a user's password
changing.

1. Administrative password reset on v2:

    POST /v2.0/users/{user_id}/OS-KSADM/password

2. Self-service password change on v2:

    PATCH /v2.0/OS-KSCRUD/users/{user_id}

3. Administrative password reset on v3:

    POST /v3/users/{user_id}

4. Self-service password change on v3:

    POST /v3/users/{user_id}/password

This patch adds additional test coverage to *consistently* ensure that:

- Old passwords no longer work
- Old tokens no longer work
- The new password works

Change-Id: I2a296b7ed407c75018fff3b60bd13aaa4fa9a849
Closes-Bug: 1407105
(cherry picked from commit a22aa08bf2176ac2da75258223f58d70303259e4)

The fernet code wasn't using seconds since the epoch correctly.
The seconds since epoch doesn't depend on the timezone, but the
time int calculated by the fernet functions was based on the local

commit_message:
Fix seconds since epoch use in fernet tokens

The fernet code wasn't using seconds since the epoch correctly.
The seconds since epoch doesn't depend on the timezone, but the
time int calculated by the fernet functions was based on the local
time of the system.

This was causing local unit tests to fail.

Closes-Bug: 1429663

commit_message:
Add Python 3.4 as supported interpreters

Rally code is python 3.4 compatible(required several small fixes, see a list
below for more details), so we can mention this great information in
setup.cfg file.

Fixed py34 incompatibe issues:
 - usage of OrderedDict for storing task results. Order of such results as
AtomicActions is important.
 - printed sla results are sorted by criterea name, so the results are equal
in all envs

Change-Id: I5f031170218ef4c2daf0ce0c2c391822218643dd
